  "texts": [
    "Then the consequent is still positive, so the result is a safe Sahlqvist implication ψ ′ k → χ ′ where ψ ′ k is a conjunction of boxed atoms and χ ′ is positive.",
    "Now we determine the local first-order correspondent of ψ ′ k → χ ′ as in the standard Sahqlvist-van Benthem algorithm, as presented in Blackburn et al.",
    "2001, Theorems 3.40, 3.42, and 3.49, except for three main differences evident from Example 6.18.",
    "First, our second-order translation has the RO( Q) constraint on each predicate variable Q; but these disappear as in Example 6.18 when we substitute the description of the minimal valuation in for Q.",
    "Second, our implications introduce universal quantification ∀x ⊑ x 0 as in Example 6.18, but that poses no problem."
